JAVA
1.Create an array with the values (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7) and shuffle it.
PROGRAM:
import java.util.Random;
public class ShuffleArray 
{
	    public static void main(String[] args) {
	        int[] a = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7};
	        
	        shuffleArray(a);	        
	        for (int i : a) {
	            System.out.print(i + " ");
	        }
	    }
	    public static void shuffleArray(int[] a) {
	        int n = a.length;
	        Random rand = new Random();

	        for (int i = n - 1; i > 0; i--) {
	            int j = rand.nextInt(i + 1);
	            
	            int temp = a[i];
	            a[i] = a[j];
	            a[j] = temp;
	        }        
	    }
}

2. Enter a Roman Number as input and convert it to an integer. (Example: IX=9).
PROGRAM:
public class RomanNumToInteger 
{
	    public static void main(String[] args) 
	    {
	        String romanNum = "iii";
	        String s=romanNum.toUpperCase();
	        int res = romanNumToInteger(s);
	        System.out.println("Integer equivalent: " + res);
	    }
	    public static int romanNumToInteger(String s) {
	        int result = 0;
	        int prevValue = 0;

	        for (int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
	            char currentChar = s.charAt(i);
	            int currValue = 0;

	            switch (currentChar) {
	                case 'I':
	                    currValue = 1;
	                    break;
	                case 'V':
	                    currValue = 5;
	                    break;
	                case 'X':
	                    currValue = 10;
	                    break;
	                case 'L':
	                    currValue = 50;
	                    break;
	                case 'C':
	                    currValue = 100;
	                    break;
	                case 'D':
	                    currValue = 500;
	                    break;
	                case 'M':
	                    currValue = 1000;
	                    break;
	            }
	            if (currValue < prevValue) {
	                result -= currValue;
	            } else {
	                result += currValue;
	            }
	            prevValue = currValue;
	        }
	        return result;
	    }
}

3. Check if the input is pangram or not. (A pangram is a sentence that contains all the alphabets from A to Z).
PROGRAM:
import java.util.Scanner;
public class PangramProgram 
{
	public static void main(String[] args) 
	{
		Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
		System.out.println("Enter String:");
		String s=scn.nextLine();
		if(pangram(s)) System.out.println("Pangram");
		else System.out.println("Not Panagram");
	}
	static boolean pangram(String st)
	{
		st=st.toUpperCase();
		for(char ch='A';ch<='Z';ch++)
		{
			if(!st.contains(ch+"")) return false;
		}
		return true;
	}
}



JAVA SCRIPT

1.Take a sentence as an input and reverse every word in that sentence.
PROGRAM:
function reverseSentence(sentence) {
    var word = sentence.split(' ');
    var reverseSentence = word.map(function(words) {
        return words.split('').reverse().join('');
    });
    var reversingSentence = reverseSentence.join(' ');

    return reversingSentence;
}
var inputSentence = "hello i am cristiano ronaldo";
var reversedSentence = reverseSentence(inputSentence);
console.log(reversedSentence);

2.Perform sorting of an array in descending order.
PROGRAM:
var numbers = [5, 2, 9, 1, 5, 6];

numbers.sort(function(a, b) {
    return b - a;
});

console.log(numbers);

HTML

1. Create a basic calculator using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with the functionality of add, subtract, multiply and divide.

HTML:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="calculator">
        <input type="text" id="display" disabled>
        <div class="buttons">

            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('7')">7</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('8')">8</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('9')">9</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('+')">+</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('4')">4</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('5')">5</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('6')">6</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('-')">-</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('1')">1</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('2')">2</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('3')">3</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('*')">*</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('0')">0</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('.')">.</button>
            <button onclick="calculateResult()">=</button>
            <button onclick="appendToDisplay('/')">/</button>
            <button onclick="clearDisplay()">AC</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

CSS:

